    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.G35/39.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have this evening impressed most earnestly upon the Cuban Minister the
                    necessity for the Cuban Government to realize its duties and responsibilities in
                    this matter and have plainly indicated to him that this Government is shocked at
                    the seeming acquiescence of the Government of Cuba in the attacks upon the
                    Legation, to be inferred by its silence thus far, and that this Government
                    expects that the Government of Cuba will promptly and adequately deal with the
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
